title: For Sale:  M145 ELCAN
postcontent: For sale or possible trade is a used ELCAN M145. This optic is very clear in like new condition. The M145 Telescope is a fixed 3.4 power, 28mm optical sight that has been designed to engage targets accurately out to 1200m range. The optical sight weighs 24 oz. (681 gr) and is extremely rugged for rough field conditions. The sight has an 8.2mm diameter exit pupil, which provides excellent vision in low light levels, i.e. dawn and dusk, and also for rapid target acquisition. The zeroing adjustment increments in both windage and elevation are 2.5 mm at 10 meters range for each detent (click of movement) and 5 inches at 500 meter range. The mount is designed to fit to the Picatinny rail MIL.Std. 1913. The optical sight has an eye relief of approximately 3 inches (70mm). Eye relief is the distance between the eye and the sight’s rear eyepiece lens. The reticle pattern has built-in trajectory compensation from 300m to 1200m range. The reticle is illuminated, by a battery. It has been used in conflicts around the world and is rated for the heaviest of machineguns, such as the M249, 240G, and MINIMI and of course M16 type rifles. This optic compares favorably against anything Leupold, Aimpoint, ACOG, or EO Tech puts out!
